727579f-a.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - Bowne Street
727579f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, south side, between Bowne and Union
Streets, showing the Aspinwall House, probably built by John
Aspinwall (about 1760), a New York merchant. It was a British
headquarters during the war for Independence.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  About 1925
